Nov 20 2009 	something you have to experience	Stayed two nights in the Phoenix with a group of 40 &quot;business industry friends&quot;.this is a rather different hotel...stayed in the past in hotels like Fairmont, Hungtington etc. and no way you can compare this hotel...it's true that the location isn't the best and probably also not the safest; I would recommend it for solo female travelers that like to do night walks, but I walked a couple of times there and had no problems.apart from that, the neighbourhood was quiet enough to get a decent sleep.the staff is very, very friendly. I checked in at 12 and my room was not ready yet. When I returned in the evening to check-in I got an upgrade to a King Suite.the room is probably more or less the same as when the hotel opened like 20 years ago. So let's call it vintage ;-). It was a large room, had most amenities except for a safe and for an A/C. So I guess on hot summer days, this might be a problem. Wifi is free but in my room (#61) it was sloooooow.there is a really affordable same day was/laundry service.the pool is small but great; they serve a free complimentary break-fast in the morning. (pastries, bagels, juice, coffee and tea, fruit)the bambuddhalounge is impressive and lively.so, it's one of these hotels you just have to try out; ideal for a short stay.	
