Jul 20 2009 	Won't stay anywhere else in SF now I've found the Phoenix a hidden gem...shhh	What a delightful little hidden gem. The most gorgeous courtyard surrounded by kitsch and quirky rooms, good sized rooms that are well furnished too! Breakfast was delicious and fresh. The courtyard was a great place for the kids to run around a bit and explore as well and jump in and out of the pool. When I think about some of the nasty accommodation I have stayed in in SF I shudder, this place is unique and I so wish I had found out about it earlier.Yes, the neighbourhood is a bit dodgy and we ended up driving to attractions instead of using the pass we had bought as I was uncomfortable taking my 10 and 7 year old past some of the less fragrant denizens of Little Saigon. They ignored us and I'm sure that we would have been absolutely okay but we just felt a little vulnerable at times...like when we got the limited stop bus by accident and had to walk 6 blocks back up to the hotel. The physical location is pretty good in the sense that it is right in the centre of town and most places aren't far away by foot, bus or car. It is a short bus ride to the nearest cable car stop and two blocks to the nearest bus stop. But when you look at the lovely hotel, the comfortable and trendy rooms, helpful and friendly staff, the great breakfast and simply beautiful courtyard this outweighs the neighbourhood. We stayed midweek for 3 nights and didn't hear any noise at all. It really was one of the nicest places I have stayed in, not the most luxurious but definitely one of the most unusual with bags of character...which I what I wanted... you can find fancy 5 star hotels anywhere and they are pretty much all the same, you could be anywhere. The Phoenix has a natural charm you can't just manufacture. Check out the postcards for the original motel... a 60s insight! We will be back...unless of course it gets too popular so...shhhhh!	
