Oct 20 2008 	So much better than the reviews led me to believe!	The staff was so helpful and friendly, even at midnight and 5 AM. The decor was fun and funky, the rooms and bathrooms clean, and the complimentary outdoor breakfast fantastic (croissants, muffins, pastries, fruit, juice, coffee and tea and real plates and utensils).After reading the reviews here, I was unnecessarily worried that I was signing up for a bad neighborhood and a barely clean room, but I didn't want to pay more for a nicer hotel. I was happily surprised at how wrong I was. The rooms and courtyard were clean and cute (and included a locked gate). There were some loiterers in the surrounding blocks, but as I dragged my suitcase past them after my midnight flight arrival, they didn't try to interact with me at all- not to panhandle, not to talk- really they just ignored me.I will definitely stay here again.	
Oct 5 2008 	Funky Friendly Phoenix	We just got back from an amazing 10 day stay at the Phoenix. It is one cool and funky hotel! The courtyard and pool live up to all the other positive reviews - it is a wonderful place to hang out (and meet other guests if you want to); swim; and/or have a few drinks after a day or night out around town. The rooms are clean and large. The staff is always helpful and very friendly.Having stayed for such an extended period - and in two different rooms in opposite corners of the hotel - we really didn't find noise to be an issue at all. It gets a little noisy on Friday and Saturday nights when the lounge is running but it never caused any trouble sleeping or enjoying the room. The staff were very good about policing the noise policy in the courtyard (it shuts down at 10 on weeknights and 11 on weekends). We noticed much more noise from the streets (lots of sirens) than from the courtyard. This is to be expected if you are staying in the heart of a major city.Remember if you are thinking about staying at the Phoenix, that you are on the edge of the Tenderloin where the city is gritty. The neighbourhood is not &quot;beautiful&quot; or touristy at all but we never felt in any danger. If you want a pasteurized San Fransico experience don't stay here. We won't be staying anywhere else on any future trips to San Francisco.	
