Feb 15 2008 	Fantastic Find Loved the Phoenix!	This is a terrific hotel in a very centrally located San Francisco neighborhood. Yes, its on the edge of the Tenderloin but a short walk down Larkin gets you to Hayes Street. Hang a right and you wind up in Hayes Valley with shopping, art, great restaurants etc. If you like walking continue from Hayes Valley on to the Haight and have a beer at Magnolia's Brewpub (Haight &amp; Masonic).The Phoenix is a reincarnation of the Caravan Motel/Motor Lodge. Cool vintage feel, fun art all around the pool and terrific staff. The Joie de Vivre &quot;chain&quot; is hugely customer oriented and folks at the Phoenix really standout in that regard.We strongly recommend this as a cool getaway spot in The City.We will definitely be back.	
