Jan 31 2008	Rock and roll motel	Really friendly, down-to-earth hotel populated by rock'n'roll wannabes and - if you believe the hype - real stars too. Not when we where there, but no matter - spacious and comfortable room overlooking a delightful swimming pool with lucious plants and faux-Thai bamboo furniture.We managed a swim, despite being January in San Fran, because the pool is heated and a short scamper from any room (they all overlook the courtyard). Al Fresco breakfast is included in the very reasonable price.The restaurant/bar is nice, too, although freeezing despite the open fire. Probably more a summer spot. Only potential problem is noise- Friday night the bar is open outside until 11pm and the walls are a little thin between the rooms, too. But a real personality hotel nonetheless, heartily recommended for the young - or young at heart.	
