Jan 13 2008 	Outstanding experience	My husband and I stayed for two nights 12/31 and 1/1/8. We were greeted by friendly and knowlegable staff who were able to direct us to a local Thai eatery. They allowed us early access to our room. One of the biggest perks with staying here is that there is FREE parking and it is centrally located. We were attending a concert three blocks away. Once we parked at the hotel we did not get back into our car until we left on the 2nd. It's several blocks to the trolley line which took us to the wharf. We then hoofed our way around the city (Chinatown) and back to the hotel. The rooms are pleasantly decorated, spacious and very clean. We loved the grounds. I didn't feel like I was in a city at all, once you enter the pool area through a secure gate (also 24 hr staff on duty). There, art and greenery abounds. We did not go in the pool (too cold) but many guest did during our stay. They don't call it the &quot;rock and roll hotel&quot; for nothing. Although the staff would not indulge me regarding any famous current guests, we did meet someone very famous while enjoying our morning breakfast. Served poolside, it is the best contental breakfast I have ever had at a hotel. The coffee was outstanding and there were fresh bagels and baked goods as well. Some fresh fruit would have been nice, though. Other than that, I can't think of anything that could have been better.	
