Sep 27 2007 	A 'find' in San Francisco	Located on the edge of the tenderloin, the Phoenix is literally an oasis with a heated pool. The staff is more than friendly and the property has been upgraded and is perfectly located for walking to the Civic Center, the Asian Art Museum, the Opera and the Symphony. The neighborhood is a bit seedy but filled with Asian restaurants and the street people can be avoided by walking a block or two away. The crowd from the lounge spills into the courtyard, but the staff is very good about cutting off the noise at 10 PM on weekdays. If you are staying over a weekend, it gets a bit rowdy around the pool until cutoff time which is later. Join the 'Joy of Life Club' (just google it) before booking a room for some extra treats and check out their other properties,,, great little hotel chain!	
