Apr 16 2007	The way to experience the REAL San Francisco!	Having been to San Francisco before, my partner and I decided that we wanted a REAL San Francisco hotel; centrally located, with some personal touches, inexpensive yet with the amenities we would pay 2 or 3X's for normally. And as for the location, sure the Tenderloin is sketchy but you are truly in the heart of EVERYTHING!Our room was pleasant and had all of the amenities any traveller would need. Yes, it was loud until early morning Sunday but hey, you should know that weekends can be that way before you go. The restaurant, Bambudda Lounge, which is actually in the hotel but not affiliated, was a great place for an ecelectic and delicious dinner. It catered to a wide variety of a crowd. And, as for the service at the Phoenix - impeccable. The front desk was very helpful on anything we asked - from restaurants to directions. Overall, we had a GRAND time in San Francisco and the Phoenix helped!Kevin PalmerFrank SchneiderChicago, IL	
