Mar 30 2007	Perfect for the girls!	One of friends found this hotel for the two San Fran nights that kicked off our girls trip. The property itself was great. Lots of interesting art and sculptures and warm and funky decorated rooms - kind of in a tiki style. The room itself just had a really colorful, fun vibe. The bedding was awesome - comfy (a priority for me), the bathrooms were clean and there was lots of space. We'd had a chance to walk a lot around the surrounding neighborhood, and I have to say I did not feel unsafe but there are more prosperous parts of town. That said, the two other gals took a run after dark and were fine. Breakfast was super, lots of choices, coffee, juice, bagels, fruit, toast, pop tarts, croissants, etc. The only thing we were unaware of was the $20 per night charge to have our 3rd person in the room. So if there are more than 2 of you, take that into account if price is a priority. One perk if you're staying in this hotel - you get free admission to the buddha lounge, adjacent to the Phoenix check in. It's a fun spot with really great music, actually. Didn't make it there the first night but stopped there the 2nd before bed and people were having a blast.	
